    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect timing in IF5 fronthaul transmission\n\n### Summary\nThe `fh_if5_south_out` function in the LTE RU was not properly accounting for timing adjustments that are critical for correct fronthaul operation. This caused incorrect data to be transmitted and timing mismatches in the IF5 interface.\n\nThe issue was that the function didn't apply the same timing corrections used in the actual RF transmission path (`tx_rf`), specifically missing the `sf_extension` and `ts_offset` adjustments.\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/lte-ru.c`: Modified `fh_if5_south_out` function to properly account for timing adjustments:\n  - Added `sf_extension` to buffer offset calculation\n  - Added `ts_offset` and `sf_extension` to timestamp calculation  \n  - Added `sf_extension` to sample count\n\nWithout this fix, users may observe:\n- Incorrect data being transmitted over IF5 interface\n- Timing misalignment between RU and RRU\n- Intermittent connection issues in TDD configurations\n- Poor RF performance in time-sensitive applications\n\nTo reproduce the issue, configure an IF5-based RU setup with TDD and monitor the transmitted samples compared to the expected timing. The mismatch becomes apparent when comparing against a working RF transmission path.\n"
}